# .exif-keeplist
#
# The only metadata tags permitted on any image in this repository.
#
# This is a KEEP-LIST, not a deny-list. The audit refuses any tag that is not
# on this list — including tags that do not exist yet. That is the point: a
# camera firmware update inventing a new location-adjacent field is blocked
# automatically, because it is not written here.
#
# The repository is public and git history is permanent. Adding a line to this
# file is a deliberate act. Do it in its own commit, so the decision is
# attributable.
#
# Groups audited: EXIF, GPS, MakerNotes, XMP, IPTC, Photoshop, JFIF, PNG, APP14.
# Groups skipped: File and Composite (derived by exiftool, not stored in the
# file), ExifTool (the scanner itself), ICC_Profile (colour management, carries
# no identity, worth keeping).

# ── What the photograph was made with ────────────────────────────
Make
Model
LensModel
LensInfo
LensMake

# ── How it was made ──────────────────────────────────────────────
FNumber
ExposureTime
ISO
FocalLength
FocalLengthIn35mmFormat
ExposureProgram
ExposureCompensation
MeteringMode
Flash

# ── When ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DateTimeOriginal
CreateDate

# ── Structural: needed to display the image correctly ────────────
# Orientation matters — drop it and portrait photos render sideways.
Orientation
ColorSpace
ExifImageWidth
ExifImageHeight
XResolution
YResolution
ResolutionUnit
ExifVersion
BitsPerSample
ColorComponents
EncodingProcess
ImageWidth
ImageHeight
JFIFVersion
YCbCrSubSampling
# Boilerplate every JPEG encoder writes. Carries no identity — these describe
# how the pixels are laid out, not who made them or where. Verified against a
# real encoder rather than assumed.
YCbCrPositioning
ComponentsConfiguration
FlashpixVersion
InteropIndex
InteropVersion
Compression
Quality
SceneCaptureType
CustomRendered
WhiteBalance
DigitalZoomRatio
SubSecTime
SubSecTimeOriginal
SubSecTimeDigitized
OffsetTime
OffsetTimeOriginal
SRGBRendering
Gamma
ColorType
BitDepth
Filter
Interlace
PixelUnits
PixelsPerUnitX
PixelsPerUnitY
SamplesPerPixel
PhotometricInterpretation
PlanarConfiguration
RowsPerStrip

# ── DELIBERATELY ABSENT — do not add without thinking hard ───────
#
#   GPS*            location. The entire reason this file exists.
#   MakerNote*      manufacturer blob. Carries body serial numbers on Nikon
#                   and Leica. Also carries Fuji's film simulation, which is
#                   genuinely nice to keep — but it lives in the same blob as
#                   the serials, and there is no safe way to keep half of it.
#                   Dropped. If this becomes annoying, that is a real feature
#                   request for crustyimg: keep-list support for named
#                   MakerNote fields.
#   SerialNumber, BodySerialNumber, LensSerialNumber, InternalSerialNumber
#   OwnerName, CameraOwnerName, Artist, Copyright, Creator, By-line
#   Software        reveals the developing toolchain; no reason to publish it
#   HostComputer    reveals the machine name
#   UserComment     free-text; can contain anything
